@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Course Guide";
}

<div class="container">
    <h1>Course Guide</h1>

    <p>
        The course has xx chapters and each chapter has subchapters.
    </p>

    <p>
        Some chapters or subchapters might contain a star (*) next to their name.
    </p>

    <p>
        If the chapter/subchapter doesn't contain a star, that means it is absolutely necessary for the course.  
        If it contains (*) 1 star, it is recommended to read and understand the concept, but not strictly required.  
        If it contains (**) 2 stars, it is advanced. It is optional and mainly for expanding knowledge.
    </p>

    <p>
        After each main chapter there will be an exercise page. The exercise page will contain tests to check your knowledge on that chapter.  
        You can answer single-choice questions or perform coding tasks.  
        There will always be an option to reveal the answer if you get stuck.
    </p>

    <p>
        In the next chapter, we will take a look at how your code should be structured so that the automatic checker can evaluate it correctly.  
        Make sure to follow the instructions strictly.
    </p>

    <div class="navigation-buttons">
        <a href="@Url.Action("Index", "Introduction")" class="btn btn-secondary ajax-link">← Introduction</a>
        <a href="@Url.Action("TaskGuide", "Introduction")" class="btn btn-primary ajax-link">Task Guide →</a>
    </div>
</div>

<style>
    .container {
        max-width: 800px;
        padding: 20px;
        background-color: var(--bs-body-bg);
        margin: 0 auto;
    }

    h1 {
        color: var(--bs-body-color);
        margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    p {
        color: var(--bs-body-color);
        line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .navigation-buttons {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        margin-top: 30px;
    }

    .btn {
        padding: 8px 20px;
        border-radius: 4px;
        font-weight: 500;
        text-decoration: none;
    }

    .btn-primary {
        background-color: var(--bs-primary);
        border-color: var(--bs-primary);
        color: #fff;
    }

    .btn-secondary {
        background-color: #6c757d;
        border-color: #6c757d;
        color: #fff;
    }
</style>
